      },
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "content": "Use this view after the overview shows LLM-side latency, errors, or fallback.\n\n- Final request rate shows the vendor/model that served the request result.\n- Attempt rate can be higher than request rate when fallback is active.\n- Attempts per request and fallback rate indicate routing quality without using cost data.\n- TTFT, generation duration, and output tokens/sec separate stream startup delay from token production speed.\n- Token usage/throughput are based only on provider-reported usage; llmgate does not tokenize prompts or responses here.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "12.3.0",
      "title": "How to analyze LLM behavior",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "prometheus"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "lineInterpolation": "linear",
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "pointSize": 4,
            "showPoints": "never"
          },
          "unit": "reqps"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 4
      },
      "id": 2,
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "list",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum by (vendor, model) (rate(llmgate_llm_requests_total[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{vendor}}/{{model}}",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Final LLM request rate",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
